                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.16044/2604.16044v1/x4.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:The overall framework of Differential Correction in Wavelet domain (DCW). At each denoising step, DPMs always generate the reconstructed sample𝒙𝜽0{\\bm{x}}_{\\bm{\\theta}}^{0}for predicting𝒙0{\\bm{x}}_{0}based on𝒙t{\\bm{x}}_{t}. After each denoising is completed, DCW maps𝒙𝜽0{\\bm{x}}_{\\bm{\\theta}}^{0}and𝒙t−1{\\bm{x}}_{t-1}to the wavelet domain via DWT to obtain𝒙𝜽f{\\bm{x}}_{\\bm{\\theta}}^{f}and𝒙t−1f{\\bm{x}}_{t-1}^{f}, wheref∈{l​l,l​h,h​l,h​h}f\\in\\{ll,lh,hl,hh\\}. Then, DCW corrects the different frequency components of𝒙t−1{\\bm{x}}_{t-1}using Eq.18. Finally, DCW maps the corrected𝒙t−1f{{\\bm{x}}}_{t-1}^{f}back to the pixel space via iDWT.",
                "position": 624
            }
        ]
